President Muhammadu Buhari is back to Abuja, Nigeria’s capital city, after spending six days in Daura, Katsina State, where he observed thebEid-el Kabir celebration. President Buhari got back to the Presidential Villa at about 11:00 hrs GMT. The President arrived in company of members of his family and personal aides. Before returning to Abuja, President Buhari received the President of neighbourong Niger Republic in Daura, where he expresses delight at the country’ exit from recession. Meanwhile, Vice President Yemi Osinbajo departed Abuja for Markurdi, the Benue State capital, to identify with survivors of the recent flood which is ravaging some parts of the State. He is expected back in Abuja later today.